<br><br><b><font color=#000099>Tinee Tank</font></b><br><b><font color=#3399EE>Highest Crit so far -- 37</font></b><br><b><font color=#990000>13th level Warrior</font></b><br><br><b><i><font color=#005511>This is your brain = [--]</font></b></i><br><b><i><font color=#005511>This is your brain on Everquest= [-LOADING..Please wait-]</font></b></i><br><b><i><font color=#005511>Any Difference?</font></b></i><br><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#DDDDAA><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualkerionfyrewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alkerion Fyrewalker</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/22/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3:03:19 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Looking for good strategies on Wiz Quad Kiting</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Welp, the way I have been doing it for awhile now is to do my quad kiting in the Burning Woods.  Plenty of mobs to kite out there.  Keep in mind tho that they have changed something with the way they work as I USED to be able to kite giants with skeles and munkies no problem.  Now I tend to run straight into disaster when I attempt to mix em like that.  Skeles and munkies mix well for a quad kite tho.<br>
<br>
The way I do it you need to have a staff of temparate flux and jboots.  I would just run around looking for blue mobs and would hit them with the staff to pull em (mana free no stop pull   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) until I've got 4 of em.  You just run in a semi tight circle with the mobs in tow so they get nice and tightly packed together for your spells.  Bonds of Force them, or more hopefully you have Atol's Spectral Shackles.<br>
<br>
Pillar of Frost them until you get to Pillar of Lightning.  Keep a draught and shock of lightning or some other low nuke loaded for finishing touches.  Rinse and repeat for phat xps.<br>
<br>
The mobs you'd prolly want to pull for your level in BW are Moldering Gorillas, Forest Giant Verdants, Greater Plague Bone Skeles, and Ember Hornets.  As you start to level up you can start doing more of Forest Giant Ancients, Greater War Bone Skeles, and Scoriae Hornets.  <br>
<br>
At 51 you are prolly safe in getting one of the harder ones mixed with the lower blues.  Two of the harder ones and you'll run out of mana long b4 the hard guys run out of health.  Alot of root parking and meding    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I've heard of some goodness in TD with raptors and kiting, but I haven't done TD myself.  /shrug<br>
